cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the privacy threats and implications of intelligent virtual assistants (IVAs) and their cloud-native data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also analyzes an experimental dataset covering three months with Alexa service, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of user lifestyle and life patterns, which can be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper presents new insights on personal information, which can be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
